Hellenic Petroleum, Larco Set to Cooperate on Renewable Energy

-- B y   P a u l   T u g w e l l
-- 
2011-07-04T15:49:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-04/hellenic-petroleum-larco-set-to-cooperate-on-renewable-energy.html
Hellenic Petroleum SA (ELPE) , Greece’s
largest refiner, said it will work with Larco Energy on
renewable energy projects starting with a photovoltaic park with
a production capacity of 17 megawatts.  Hellenic’s renewable energy unit, ELPE Renewables, will
hold 51 percent of any companies set up to develop renewable
energy projects while Larco Energy, a unit of Greek miner  Larco
SA , which is  Europe ’s largest ferronickel producer, will have a
49 percent stake, Athens-based Hellenic Petroleum said today in
an e-mailed statement.  The collaboration with Larco is part of Hellenic’s
strategic goal to produce electricity from renewable sources
equivalent to 100 megawatts over the next three years, according
to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Paul Tugwell in Athens 
